</table><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Hey <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/27837758.260614/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9u=
ZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMjUvZG8ta3dvbi13aW5zLWJhY2tpbmctZm9yLWhpcy1wcm9=
wb3NhbC10by1yZXNjdWUtdGVycmEtcHJvamVjdD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNTI1MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRi=
Z1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjA1MjUmd=
XRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB96a04a7a" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
Terra=C2=A0is doing stuff</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
A proposal by the founder of the troubled Terra ecosystem to salvage the pr=
oject was approved, averting a total collapse of one of the most-watched ex=
periments in decentralized finance.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">U=
nder Do Kwon=E2=80=99s newly approved structure, the original blockchain wi=
ll be known as Terra Classic, while its native token Luna, which plunged cl=
ose to zero this month, will be renamed Luna Classic with the ticker LUNC. =
The new Terra blockchain will start running a coin under the existing Luna =
name and ticker, and won=E2=80=99t include the TerraUSD stablecoin</p><p st=
yle=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Terra=E2=80=99s unraveling, which started earlier t=
his month with the implosion of the algorithmic stablecoin Kwon had touted =
relentlessly, marked one of the biggest busts in the crypto industry=E2=80=
=99s history. While the outcome of Wednesday=E2=80=99s vote represents a vi=
ctory of sorts for Kwon and his supporters, doubts persist about whether Te=
rra can ultimately be revived.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The pr=
ocess means Terraform Labs is effectively abandoning the stablecoin TerraUS=
D, or UST, which from now on will only trade on the Terra Classic blockchai=
n. Designed to maintain a 1-to-1 peg to the dollar, it traded at around 10 =
cents on Wednesday.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We have ta=
lked a few times recently about=C2=A0Terra, the blockchain ecosystem whose =
<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27837758.260614/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTEvdGVyc=
mEtZmxvcHM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyNTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1f=
c291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNTI1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZ=
m/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8411a5cd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> algorithmic stablecoin</a> bl=
ew up <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27837758.260=
614/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTI=
vY3J5cHRvLWNyYXNoLWNvbnRhZ2lvbi1jb3VsZC1nby1iZXlvbmQtYml0Y29pbi1ldGhlcmV1bS=
10ZXRoZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDUyNTIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc=
291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIwNTI1JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB629c5fd6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">earlier this month</a>. One mod=
el of Terra=C2=A0goes like this:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; =
padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">T=
erra is a company. Not really =E2=80=94=C2=A0it=E2=80=99s a decentralized f=
inance ecosystem, a blockchain, a bunch of independent developers working o=
n diverse projects =E2=80=94=C2=A0but let=E2=80=99s just pretend for a minu=
te. (In fact there is a company-ish thing called Terraform Labs which helps=
 run Terra, and another company-ish thing called Luna Foundation Guard that=
 keeps some of Terra=E2=80=99s money, but here I want to conceive of Terra =
as a whole as sort of a distributed company.)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bo=
ttom: 5px;">The Luna token, which powers the Terra blockchain and is the cu=
rrency of its ecosystem, is the=C2=A0<em>equity=C2=A0</em>of Terra, the sto=
ck in the Terra company.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The Terra=
USD stablecoin (or UST), which was supposed to always be worth a dollar, an=
d which maintained that peg by being exchangeable for $1 worth of Luna at m=
arket prices, is the=C2=A0<em>debt=C2=A0</em>of Terra. Like bonds of the co=
mpany, or like deposits of a bank.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Th=
is model has a lot going for it. UST, certainly, looks like debt: You buy a=
 UST for a fixed amount ($1), and you expect to get back that fixed amount =
($1), and while you hold it you earn interest. (For a while, you could <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/27837758.260614/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cubm90Ym9yaW5nLmNvL3AvdGVycmEtdG8tdGhlLW1vb24tYW5kLWJhY2s_cz1y/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2782f1b3" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !import=
ant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-=
style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">get 19.5% interest</a> on UST in the=
 Anchor protocol, a part of the Terra ecosystem.) It was advertised as a sa=
fe investment, a way to participate in the Terra ecosystem with a guarantee=
 of getting your money back.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Luna, meanwhil=
e, looks like equity. It has no fixed value; it went up as optimism about T=
erra grew, and went down as Terra imploded. Luna could go to zero if Terra =
failed, or it could go to the moon if Terra became the world=E2=80=99s domi=
nant financial system. There was no floor and no cap on Luna=E2=80=99s valu=
e (unlike UST, which was floored and capped at $1); it was just worth some =
fraction of the future value of the Terra ecosystem.</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 16px 0;">There are some implications of this model. One implication is tha=
t you=C2=A0might think: Wait, if these coins are the debt and equity of a c=
ompany, aren=E2=80=99t they securities? If they are securities, and they we=
re sold to US investors, aren=E2=80=99t they required to be registered with=
 the US Securities and Exchange Commission? If they are securities that wer=
e sold broadly to the general public and then lost almost all of their valu=
e, shouldn=E2=80=99t the SEC investigate? If big US crypto trading firms an=
d venture capitalists were buying huge piles of Luna from Terra=E2=80=99s p=
romoters=C2=A0and dumping them to retail buyers on exchanges while also tal=
king up Terra, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/278=
